<p><b>Snow</b> is a type of <a href="/wiki/Precipitation_(meteorology)" title="Precipitation (meteorology)">precipitation</a> in the form of <a href="/wiki/Crystal" title="Crystal">crystalline</a> <a href="/wiki/Water" title="Water">water</a> <a href="/wiki/Ice" title="Ice">ice</a>, consisting of a multitude of snowflakes that fall from <a href="/wiki/Cloud" title="Cloud">clouds</a>. The process of this precipitation is called <b>snowfall</b>.</p>
<p>Since snow is composed of small ice particles, it is a <a href="/wiki/Granular_material" title="Granular material">granular material</a>. It has an open and therefore soft structure, unless packed by external <a href="/wiki/Pressure" title="Pressure">pressure</a>.</p>
